{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T15:23:24.659Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-shot prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" is the simplest form of prompting. It's when you give a gen AI tool "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"instructions without giving any examples"},{"type":"text","text":". You rely entirely on the model's existing knowledge and instruction-following capabilities to complete the task."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The term \"shot\" equals an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"example"},{"type":"text","text":". Zero-shot = no examples. One-shot = one example. Few-shot = several examples."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What Zero-Shot Means"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-shot prompting means that the prompt used to interact with the model won't contain examples or demonstrations."},{"type":"text","text":" The zero-shot prompt directly instructs the model to perform a task without any additional examples to steer it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instruction: Classify the text into neutral, negative, or positive.\nText: I think the food was okay.\nSentiment:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in the prompt above we didn't provide the model with any examples of text alongside their classifications—the LLM already understands \"sentiment\" from its pretraining. That's the zero-shot capability at work."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key Characteristics of Zero-Shot"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Characteristic"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot Value"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simplest approach"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token usage"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low (reduces number of tokens created)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low (helps control costs)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reliance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model's pretraining and instruction tuning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High (works for lots of different tasks)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How Zero-Shot Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Large language models (LLMs) today, such as GPT-3.5 Turbo, GPT-4, and Claude 3, are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tuned to follow instructions and are trained on large amounts of data"},{"type":"text","text":". Large-scale training makes these models capable of performing some tasks in a \"zero-shot\" manner."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Instruction tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" has been shown to improve zero-shot learning. Instruction tuning is essentially the concept of finetuning models on datasets described via instructions. Furthermore, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RLHF (reinforcement learning from human feedback)"},{"type":"text","text":" has been adopted to scale instruction tuning wherein the model is aligned to better fit human preferences."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to Use Zero-Shot"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Primary Use Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Work with fine-tuned LLMs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Because zero-shot learning relies on the model's existing knowledge, it's not as resource-intensive as few-shot learning, and it works well with LLMs that have already been fine-tuned on instruction datasets."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":" When you have a model that's already trained on instruction data (like Claude, GPT-4). You might be able to rely solely on zero-shot learning and keep costs relatively low."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Establish performance baselines"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero-shot learning can help you simulate how your app would perform for actual users. This lets you evaluate various aspects of your model's current performance, such as accuracy or precision."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":" Use zero-shot learning to establish a performance baseline and then experiment with few-shot learning to improve performance."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"General Guidelines"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-shot works for lots of different tasks, and it is a good starting point."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use zero-shot when:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is simple and well-defined"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to test the model's baseline performance"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're working with a fine-tuned model (like Claude, GPT-4)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to minimize token usage and cost"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is something the model likely knows from pretraining (e.g., sentiment analysis, summarization)"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 1: Sentiment Classification"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instruction: Classify the text into neutral, negative, or positive.\nText: I think the food was okay.\nSentiment:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that we didn't provide examples of text alongside their classifications. The LLM already understands \"sentiment\" from its pretraining—that's zero-shot at work."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 2: Summarization"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summarize this user feedback:\n\"I love the product but it's too expensive. The reporting feature is slow. I'd love a dark mode.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No examples needed. The model understands what \"summarize\" means from its pretraining."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 3: Translation"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Translate the following sentence to French:\n\"Hello, how are you?\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model already knows French and understands the concept of \"translate\" from pretraining."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 4: Intent Classification"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instruction: Evaluate user input to determine which of four possible intents the input represents.\nThe four possible intents are:\n1. Purchase\n2. Refund\n3. Support\n4. Inquiry\n\nInput: \"I want to buy a new laptop.\"\n\nOutput:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This tells the model to evaluate input and determine intent, but doesn't provide examples. The model relies on pretraining."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 5: Code Generation"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a Python function that calculates the factorial of a number."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No examples needed. The model understands what \"factorial\" means and how to write Python code from pretraining."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot vs. Few-Shot: When to Level Up"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Nowadays zero-shot works for lots of different tasks, and it is a good starting point. However, if your results are poor, you'll need to level up to one-shot prompting."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When zero-shot doesn't work, it's recommended to provide demonstrations or examples in the prompt, which leads to few-shot prompting."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Comparison"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":"left"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2+ examples"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token usage"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Higher"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Baseline"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can improve performance"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple tasks, baseline testing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex tasks, ambiguous formats"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reliance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model's pretraining"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Examples + pretraining"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best Practices for Zero-Shot Prompting"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on research from \"A Practical on Zero Prompt Design In-context Learning\":"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Simplicity and Clarity"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompts should be expressed in straightforward language, avoiding ambiguity or jargon. The expected output format should be clearly indicated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"BAD: \"Could you maybe write something about a science topic?\"\nGOOD: \"Write a 200-word summary of the effects of climate change on coastal cities.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Explicit Constraints"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clearly outline any limitations, guidelines, or specific criteria for the output. This helps keep the LLM's responses relevant and accurate."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Write a 3-paragraph email. Each paragraph should be 2-3 sentences. Total under 150 words.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Task Decomposition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Split complex tasks into smaller, more digestible components. This \"divide and conquer\" strategy can greatly enhance precision."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"BAD: \"Build me a user signup feature and also show some stats on usage.\"\nGOOD: \"First, implement a user sign-up form with email and password. Then, after successful signup, display a dashboard showing user count statistics.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Role-Playing/Personas"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Direct the LLM to assume a particular role or persona. This shapes the response's style, tone, and content."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"You are a senior TypeScript engineer. Review this code for concurrency issues.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Output Format Specification"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clearly specify the anticipated format (e.g., bullet points, tables, JSON). This promotes consistency."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Return valid JSON with fields: category, reason, confidence.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Chain-of-Thought (CoT)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Encourage the LLM to clearly outline its reasoning process step-by-step. Phrases like \"Let's think step by step\" or \"Explain your reasoning\" can significantly boost performance on intricate tasks."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Let's think step by step. First, explain what this function does. Then identify issues. Finally, propose a fix.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Common Mistakes with Zero-Shot"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 1: Being Too Vague"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Help me with my code. It's broken.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"You are a senior Python engineer. I'm building a FastAPI backend. The API crashes when handling large JSON payloads. Explain the bug and propose a fix.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 2: Not Specifying Output Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this text.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this text in exactly 3 bullet points, each under 20 words.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mistake 3: Using Ambiguous Language"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Tell me about dogs.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"List 5 unique facts about Golden Retrievers, in bullet points.\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-shot prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" is the simplest prompting technique:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": Instructions without examples"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Simple tasks, fine-tuned models, baseline testing, cost minimization"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":": Relies on model's pretraining and instruction tuning"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits"},{"type":"text","text":": Low token usage, low cost, high flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to level up"},{"type":"text","text":": When results are poor, move to one-shot or few-shot prompting"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key principles:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simplicity and Clarity"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use straightforward language"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit Constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" — Define limitations and criteria"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task Decomposition"},{"type":"text","text":" — Break complex tasks into steps"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role-Playing"},{"type":"text","text":" — Assign a persona to the model"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output Format"},{"type":"text","text":" — Specify the expected format"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain-of-Thought"},{"type":"text","text":" — Encourage step-by-step reasoning"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero-shot is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"best starting point"},{"type":"text","text":" for most tasks because it's simple, cost-effective, and works well with modern instruction-tuned models like Claude."}]}]}}
